==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Propinquity
<hw>Pro*pin"qui*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>propinquitas</ets>, from <ets>propinquus</ets> near, neighboring,
from <ets>prope</ets> near.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Nearness in place; neighborhood;
proximity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Nearness in time.</def> <rj><au>Sir T.
Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Nearness of blood; kindred; affinity.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Propinyl</ent>⟦br⟧
